<subSubSection id="C7CE65215F3C5210FF10FEE1FEE7135B" pageId="2" pageNumber="1121" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8F6B36AA5F3C5210FF10FEE1FEE7135B" blockId="2.[178,1086,363,531]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1121">
Comment: In a recent paper, 
<bibRefCitation id="EB454B5B5F3C5210FD98FEE1FD2510C9" author="BORDONI A" box="[570,744,363,385]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1121" pagination="49 - 58" refId="ref6240" refString="BORDONI A. (2013): Observations on some Staphylinidae and new synonymies (Coleoptera). - Fragmenta Entomologica 45 (1 - 2): 49 - 58." type="journal article" year="2013">BORDONI (2013)</bibRefCitation>
proposed several, partly rather bizarre synonymies, among them the (repeated) synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="48D44D295F3C5210FCC1FE03FC1210D5" authorityName="ZANETTI" authorityYear="1998" box="[867,991,392,414]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Tetartopeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ciceronii">
<emphasis id="BDA0EAB85F3C5210FCC1FE03FC1210D5" box="[867,991,392,414]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1121">T. ciceronii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="48D44D295F3C5210FB8AFE03FE0610F3" authority="REITTER (1909)" authorityName="REITTER" authorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Tetartopeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufonitidus">
<emphasis id="BDA0EAB85F3C5210FB8AFE03FEEC10F2" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1121">T. rufonitidus</emphasis>
REITTER (1909)
</taxonomicName>
, without providing any new evidence whatsoever. As argued in detail earlier (
<bibRefCitation id="EB454B5B5F3C5210FECAFE49FE3A1091" author="ASSING V" box="[360,503,451,473]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1121" pagination="1237 - 1294" refId="ref5937" refString="ASSING V. (2008): On the taxonomy and zoogeography of some Palaearctic Paederinae and Xantholinini (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 40 (2): 1237 - 1294." type="journal article" year="2008">ASSING 2008</bibRefCitation>
), 
<emphasis id="BDA0EAB85F3C5210FDACFE49FD4C1090" box="[526,641,451,472]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1121">T. ciceroni</emphasis>
undoubtedly represents a distinct species differing from 
<taxonomicName id="48D44D295F3C5210FEFBFE6AFE2610BD" authorityName="REITTER" authorityYear="1909" box="[345,491,480,501]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Tetartopeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufonitidus">
<emphasis id="BDA0EAB85F3C5210FEFBFE6AFE2610BD" box="[345,491,480,501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1121">T. rufonitidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in numerous constant characters and is consequently revalidated.
</paragraph>
